<taxonomicName LSID="http://species-id.net/wiki/Daphniola_exigua" authority="A. Schmidt, 1856" authorityName="A. Schmidt" authorityYear="1856" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola exigua" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exigua">Daphniola exigua (A. Schmidt, 1856)</taxonomicName>
Figure 3
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
A large population of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola exigua" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exigua">Daphniola exigua</taxonomicName>
was found in Ag. Paraskevi spring, Tempi valley, Nom. Larissas where anthropogenic activity is high. Ag. Paraskevi spring is one of the two known localities where the species is distributed (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuett, H" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="115 - 149" title="Zur Kenntnis griechischer Hydrobiiden." volume="110" year="1980">
<normalizedToken originalValue="SchÃ¼tt">Schuett</normalizedToken>
1980
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="2301 - 2311" title="Daphniola Radoman, 1973 (Gastropoda: Hydrobiidae): shell biometry, mtDNA, and the Pliocene flooding." url="10.1080/00222930701630733" volume="41" year="2007">Falniowski et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The other locality is Daphni spring, close to Ag. Paraskevi (
<bibRefCitation author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Posebna Izdanja, Prirodnjacki Musej u Beogradu" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 30" title="New classification of fresh and brackish water Prosobranchia from the Balkans and Asia Minor." volume="32" year="1973">Radoman 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Department of Sciences" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="Hydrobioidea, a Superfamily of Prosobranchia (Gastropoda)" volumeTitle="Monographs DXLVII" year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="2301 - 2311" title="Daphniola Radoman, 1973 (Gastropoda: Hydrobiidae): shell biometry, mtDNA, and the Pliocene flooding." url="10.1080/00222930701630733" volume="41" year="2007">Falniowski et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Posebna Izdanja, Prirodnjacki Musej u Beogradu" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 30" title="New classification of fresh and brackish water Prosobranchia from the Balkans and Asia Minor." volume="32" year="1973">Radoman (1973)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Daphniola</taxonomicName>
from the latter spring, the type species being 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola graeca" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">Daphniola graeca</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Falniowski, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="2301 - 2311" title="Daphniola Radoman, 1973 (Gastropoda: Hydrobiidae): shell biometry, mtDNA, and the Pliocene flooding." url="10.1080/00222930701630733" volume="41" year="2007">Falniowski et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, using morphological and COI sequence data, showed that 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola exigua" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exigua">Daphniola exigua</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola graeca" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">Daphniola graeca</taxonomicName>
are conspecific both belonging to 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Daphniola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Daphniola exigua" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exigua">Daphniola exigua</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
